    <item>
      <title>Colour Palette</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/colour-palette/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 19 Jun 2026 18:21:47 +1000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/colour-palette/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;You don&amp;rsquo;t get far if you don&amp;rsquo;t give yourself a good colour palette.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;That&amp;rsquo;s why one of the first things I did was set up one of my own.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;palette-grid&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;swatch&#34; style=&#34;background:#000000;&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;swatch-text light&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;strong&gt;Black&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&#xA;      #000000&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;swatch&#34; style=&#34;background:#0F3653;&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;swatch-text light&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;strong&gt;Dark Blue&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&#xA;      #0F3653&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;swatch&#34; style=&#34;background:#332F41;&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;swatch-text light&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;strong&gt;Dark Purple&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&#xA;      #332F41&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;swatch&#34; style=&#34;background:#FFFFFF; border:1px solid #ddd;&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;swatch-text dark&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;strong&gt;White&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&#xA;      #FFFFFF&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;swatch&#34; style=&#34;background:#80CDF3;&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;swatch-text dark&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;strong&gt;Light Blue&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&#xA;      #80CDF3&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;swatch&#34; style=&#34;background:#EBC06F;&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;swatch-text dark&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;strong&gt;Pale Yellow&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&#xA;      #EBC06F&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;br&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The main colours used would be Dark Blue and Light Blue (as you can see on my logo). While it would have been fine to stick to a blue gradient, I added Dark Purple and Pale Yellow in case if I ever needed more colours.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I checked all of the colour contrast of each colour using &lt;a href=&#34;https://webaim.org/resources/contrastchecker/&#34;&gt;WebAIM Contrast Checker&lt;/a&gt;. While I&amp;rsquo;m aiming for WCAG AA compliance across this website, I&amp;rsquo;ll take the extra step and go with AAA compliance for colour contrast.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The light colours should all have sufficient contrast against Black, and all the dark colours should have sufficient contrast against White.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
